    <abstract id="aspace_d3acc826be648141e79137bbd2209730" label="Abstract">DeWayne Lundgren, a Brooklyn, New York resident, was a private in the United States Army, serving in the 830th Signal Service Company during World War Two. After training in Fort Monmouth, NJ, he was posted to Africa and England 1943 - 1945. This collection contains approximately 232 letters from DeWayne to his girlfriend, Bertha Doktor, plus newsletters from Africa, <title render="italic">The Stars and Stripes</title> clippings, and a few of Bertha's letters to DeWayne.</abstract>
